---
import SectionWithImage from '../../ui/SectionWithImage.astro'
import Col from '../../../components/ui/Col.astro'
import Row from '../../../components/ui/Row.astro'
import powerlines from '../../../assets/powerlines-3.jpg'
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components'
---

<SectionWithImage
	id="gridscore-hero"
	image={powerlines}
	imageAlt="Modern electrical substation with high-voltage lines and insulators under a clear blue sky, technical high-end industrial photography"
	mode="light"
	surfaceColor
	reverse
>
	<Row>
		<Col span="12" classes="relative z-10">
			<p class="mb-4 font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-primary-500">
				Strategic Context
			</p>
			<h2 class="mb-8 font-headings text-3xl font-bold leading-tight lg:text-4xl">
				Why grid data matters now
			</h2>
			<p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
				As grid connection queues increase across Germany, project viability depends more than ever
				on understanding congestion exposure, network constraints, and regional capacity dynamics
				before capital is deployed.
			</p>
			<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
				GridScore supports developers and investors with structured grid intelligence to improve
				siting decisions, prioritise development resources, and reduce hidden connection risk.
			</p>
			<ul class="space-y-4">
				<li class="flex items-center gap-3 font-semibold text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-200">
					<Icon name="check-circle" class="h-5 w-5 text-primary-500" />
					Mitigate grid connection risk
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-center gap-3 font-semibold text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-200">
					<Icon name="check-circle" class="h-5 w-5 text-primary-500" />
					Evaluate regional grid constraints
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-center gap-3 font-semibold text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-200">
					<Icon name="check-circle" class="h-5 w-5 text-primary-500" />
					Prioritize stronger connection sites
				</li>
			</ul>
		</Col>
	</Row>
</SectionWithImage>
